lavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Like   Jane   and   Joan  , a medieval variant of Old French <i>Je(h)anne</i>. Towards the end of the Middle Ages this form became largely confined to Scotland. In the 20th century it became more widely used in the English-speaking world and enjoyed a period of great popularity, but it is now out of fashion. Among numerous well-known and influential bearers are the British novelists  Jean Plaidy  (  Eleanor Hibbert ,  1910–93 ) and  Jean Rhys  (  Ella Gwendolen Rees Williams ,  1894–1979 ), British actress  Jean Simmons  (  1929–2010 ), and American-born actress  Jean Seberg  (  1938–79 ). It is also found as a variant spelling of the masculine name   Gene ."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."]},{"name":"Jeane","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Jean ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Jean de Vendôme was born in 1230, in Vendôme, Loir-et-Cher, France, his father, Comte Pierre de Vendôme I, was 30 and his mother, Jeanne Gervaise de Mayenne, was 25. He had at least 1 son with Alix du Fresnes. He died in 1283, at the age of 53."},"et":{"1230–1283":"1230–1283","1210–1270":"1210–1270","1227–1292":"1227–1292","1235–1286":"1235–1286","1235–Female":"1235–Surnud","1256–1315":"1256–1315","1200–1249":"1200–1249","1205–1247":"1205–1247","1286":"1286","1230":"1230","1283":"1283","1292":"1292","1270":"1270","13 MAR 1256":"13. märts 1256","1228":"1228","1205":"1205","1249":"1249","1315":"1315","1227":"1227","1247":"1247","1235":"1235","1256":"1256","1200":"1200","1210":"1210","April 17 1247":"17. aprill 1247","25 March 1249":"25. märts 1249","Vendôme,41269,Loir-et-Cher,Centre-Val de Loire,FRANCE,":"Vendôme, Loir-et-Cher, Centre, Prantsusmaa","Vendôme, Loir-et-Cher, Centre-Val de Loire, France":"Vendôme, Loir-et-Cher, Prantsusmaa","Cyprus":"Küpros"},"fi":{"1230–1283":"1230–1283","1210–1270":"1210–